commitResults.messageBody:
- UniqueClassList and UniqueStudentList are now HashMaps
- The AddCommand handles the logic for creating a class
  How this works is that a class is _always_ created when doing add
  command parsing. Only when the `execute` command of the AddCommand is
  done, it checks whether the timing is the same as the one to be added
  and adds the Student to the Class and the Class to the Student.

commitResults.messageBody:
- Made findtag keywords be split by commas, to allow searching for multi word tags eg. searching for 'A Math' and not 'C Math'
- Modified findtag and findname to allow for partial matches, so user can search for 'math' and get 'A Math'
- Improved sample data to use subject tags, have realistic emails, have different NOKs with similar addresses
- Added some classes to sample data with realistic timings, names, locations and rates

commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, the 'removefromclass' command uses the student indices as shown in the student list.
This is counterintuitive as the user is likely to be looking at the student list in the class tab when performing this operation.
So let us change the student indices as used in the command to used the ones shown in the class tab of the class to be removed from.
